[B] Death total
Date: Fri 27 Aug 2021 08:59 EDT
Source: Miami Herald [abridged, edited]
https://www.miamiherald.com/news/coronavirus/article253766203.html


Florida on Thursday [26 Aug 2021] reported 21 765 more COVID-19 cases and 901 deaths to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), according to Miami Herald calculations of CDC data.

All but 2 of the newly reported deaths occurred after 25 Jul 2021, with about 78% of those people dying in the past 2 weeks, according to Herald calculations of data published by the CDC. The majority of deaths happened during Florida's latest surge in COVID-19 cases, fueled by the delta variant.

It is the largest single-day increase to the death total in the state's COVID pandemic history. In the last 7 days, on average, the state has added 242 deaths and 22 556 cases each day, according to Herald calculations.

The jump in the number of reported cases and deaths is due to the newest way deaths and cases are counted. The CDC implemented the change earlier this month [August 2021], causing occasional one-day aberrations like the 901 additional deaths on Thursday [26 Aug 2021] and 726 more deaths reported Monday [23 Aug 2021].

In all, Florida has recorded at least 3 151 909 confirmed COVID cases statewide and 43 632 deaths.

As of the Thursday [26 Aug 2021] report, 11 138 433 eligible Floridians -- 51.9% of the state's population -- had completed the 2-dose series of Pfizer-BioNTech or Moderna, or have completed Johnson & Johnson's single-dose vaccine, according to the CDC.

[Byline: Devoun Cetoute]

