[5] Regional update: ProMED SoAs
[A] Bangladesh
Date: Fri 27 Aug 2021 00:00 BST
Source: The Daily Star [edited]
https://www.thedailystar.net/health/disease/coronavirus/news/covid-pandemic-infection-rate-drops-1377pc-2161816


Bangladesh, currently seeing a downtrend in COVID-19 cases, detected 4698 fresh cases in 34 111 samples in the last 24 hours as of yesterday morning [26 Aug 2021]. The positivity rate dropped to 13.77%. The country last reported a 13.39% daily positivity rate on 11 Jun 2021.

Besides, 102 more deaths were reported during the 24-hour period, according to the Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS). The fresh numbers took the country's death tally to 25 729 and caseload to 1 482 628.

The recovery rate rose to 94.38%, but the case fatality also rose to 1.74% compared to the same period. Among the new deaths, 37 died in Dhaka division, 24 in Chattogram, 13 in Sylhet, and 8 in Khulna division.

