[B] India
Date: Fri 27 Aug 2021 05:08 IST
Source: The Times of India, Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/kerala-logs-30k-cases-for-2nd-day-india-count-tops-44500/articleshow/85674761.cms


Kerala recorded 30 000-plus fresh COVID-19 cases for the 2nd day running, taking India's daily count to over 44 500 on Thursday [26 Aug 2021].

India reported 44 510 fresh cases of the virus, with Kerala alone accounting for 30 007 new infections. The state had recorded 31 445 cases on Wednesday [25 Aug 2021], making it the 1st state in nearly 3 months (since 29 May 2021) to register more than 30 000 fresh infections in a day. India's daily count of COVID cases had crossed 46 000 on Wednesday [25 Aug 2021].

With the number of cases exploding after the Onam week, Kerala reported a test positivity rate (TPR) of over 18% on Thursday [26 Aug 2021]. The TPR [test positivity rate] in the state has been steadily rising, indicating that infections may still be on the rise.

Meanwhile, Maharashtra logged more than 5000 new cases for the 2nd day in a row. The state recorded 5108 fresh COVID infections on Thursday [26 Aug 2021], up slightly from the previous day's tally of 5031. Prior to Wednesday [25 Aug 2021], Maharashtra's daily count of cases had remained below 5000 for 5 days. Despite the seeming surge, daily numbers in the state have remained lower than the corresponding days of the previous week.

Andhra Pradesh and Bengal too were witnessing a minor surge in infections since Wednesday [25 Aug 2021]. Andhra Pradesh reported 1539 cases on Thursday [26 Aug 2021] and 1601 on Wednesday, both numbers slightly higher than last week's peak of 1501. Bengal logged 717 and 708 in the last 2 days. These numbers, however, were lower than the previous week's peak.

India recorded 486 deaths from the virus on Thursday [26 Aug 2021], down from the previous day's surprisingly high toll of 603. Kerala reported 162 fatalities, Maharashtra 159, Odisha 66, Tamil Nadu 26, and Karnataka 25.

With new infections outnumbering recoveries in the last 3 days, active cases in the country have increased by more than 22 000 since Monday [23 Aug 2021] to over 3.4 lakh [340 000] on Thursday [26 Aug 2021].

