[C] Nepal
Date: Thu 26 Aug 2021 16:38 NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepal-reports-2052-cases-26-deaths-recovery-rate-at-935


Nepal's coronavirus caseload reached 754 915 on Thursday [26 Aug 2021] with 2052 more people testing positive for the infection in the past 24 hours. Meanwhile, the total coronavirus recoveries stand at 705 893 with 1929 discharges logged today [26 Aug 2021]. On the other hand, the countrywide COVID-19 mortality toll increased to 10 638 with 26 more fatalities.

As per the latest data provided by the health ministry, 14 374 total tests were conducted in the last 24 hours of which 9702 were PCR tests while 4672 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 3 868 717 PCR tests have been carried out to date [26 Aug 2021].

Similarly, antigen tests have confirmed 381 positive cases in the past 24 hours. The total number of single-day infections from both the RT-PCR and antigen tests amount to 2433.

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate stands at 93.5%, while the fatality rate stands at 1.5%. The country's active COVID-19 case count currently is 38 384.

So far, a total of 8 936 422 people has received coronavirus vaccine across the country, of which 4 986 893 have received the 1st dose while only 3 949 529 individuals have been inoculated with both the doses and are fully vaccinated.

Currently, there are 366 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal. In the same time frame, 515 infections were reported in the capital city while Lalitpur and Bhaktapur reported 88 and 142 cases, respectively.

On Wednesday [25 Aug 2021], Nepal's coronavirus caseload had reached 752 863 with 1862 people testing positive for the infection.

