[E] Sri Lanka
Date: Fri 27 Aug 2021 07:11 IST
Source: Daily Mirror [edited]
https://www.dailymirror.lk/latest_news/Extension-of-nationwide-lockdown-Decision-today/342-219113


A decision will be taken today [27 Aug 2021] whether the countrywide lockdown will be further extended after Monday [30 Aug 2021] when the COVID-19 Task Force convenes with President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, Health Minister Keheliya Rambukwella told Daily Mirror yesterday [26 Aug 2021].

In a meeting held between Rambukwella and the health trade unions yesterday morning [26 Aug 2021], it was discussed that extending the lockdown further would not serve many purposes as the only way out of the crisis was to ensure that all citizens are fully vaccinated as soon as possible, the Daily Mirror learns.

Rambukwella at the meeting had informed that he was personally against the lockdown as it severely affected the economy and the livelihoods of the daily wage earners, but a final decision will be taken today after due consideration of the opinion of all experts.

He said that according to scientific evidence, the moment a lockdown is enforced there is a slight decline of the cases, however, COVID-19 begins to spread once the country re-opens once again, "so where do we draw the line?" he questioned.

The minister further said that vaccination and self-discipline were the only way out of this pandemic and authorities would continue to administer the doses until the targets are achieved. "According to the figures I received, less than 2% of those fully vaccinated have died from the virus while 12.5% of those who received the 1st dose have died of COVID-19; 86% of the deaths were of those who were not vaccinated," he said.

At today's meeting [27 Aug 2021], the Daily Mirror learns that a proposal will also be submitted if area-wise lockdowns could be enforced rather than extending the nationwide lockdown. President Gotabaya Rajapaksa will announce the final decision today following the meeting. If the lockdown is not extended, it will be lifted on Monday [30 Aug 2021] at 4:00 am.

[Byline: Jamila A. Husain]

