Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 27 Aug 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20AUG27_1630164494.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 39.0% of daily case numbers and 42.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 82.86 million cases. The USA reported over 169 000 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Brazil (30 671) and Mexico (21 250); 10 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 26.0% of daily case numbers and 19.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 64.51 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (2 cases), Switzerland (6 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others; 20 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 11 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.8% of daily case numbers and 10.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 14.37 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (36 758) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Tunisia, Libya, and Occupied Palestinian Territory. UAE reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 3.7% of daily case numbers and 6.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.56 million cases. South Africa (12 771) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours, followed by Botswana and Ethiopia. Cameroon, Algeria, Kenya, Ghana, Nigeria, and Rwanda reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Reunion, Uganda, Gabon, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 12.6% of daily case numbers and 11.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.22 million cases. Japan reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 26 000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Philippines, Viet Nam, South Korea, Australia, Fiji, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 9.6% of the daily newly reported cases and 8.5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 40.91 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 44 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (18 702). Indonesia, Bangladesh, Myanmar, and Nepal did not report cases over the last 3 days. Additionally, Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases for many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 27 Aug 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

